## 1. 🔌 Service Running Check

Sabse pehle check karo ki DB service chal rahi hai ya nahi.

**PostgreSQL:**
```bash
sudo systemctl status postgresql
sudo systemctl start postgresql      # agar band ho
sudo systemctl enable postgresql     # auto-start on boot
```

**Oracle:**
```bash
lsnrctl status
lsnrctl start                        # agar band ho
```

---

## 2. 🌐 Port Open Check

DB sahi port pe sun raha hai ya nahi.

**PostgreSQL (Default Port: 5432):**
```bash
netstat -tlnp | grep 5432
# ya
ss -tlnp | grep 5432
```

**Oracle (Default Port: 1521):**
```bash
netstat -tlnp | grep 1521
# ya
ss -tlnp | grep 1521
```

---

## 3. 🔥 Firewall Check

Firewall DB port block toh nahi kar raha.

**UFW (Ubuntu/Debian):**
```bash
# PostgreSQL
sudo ufw allow 5432
sudo ufw status

# Oracle
sudo ufw allow 1521
sudo ufw status
```

**Firewalld (CentOS/RHEL):**
```bash
# PostgreSQL
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=5432/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

# Oracle
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=1521/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload
```

---

## 4. 👤 Credentials Check

Username, password aur hostname sahi hain ya nahi.

**PostgreSQL:**
```bash
psql -U username -d dbname -h hostname -p 5432
```

**Oracle:**
```bash
sqlplus username/password@hostname:1521/servicename
```

> ⚠️ **Note:** Password mein special characters hain toh quotes use karo.

