## 5. 📄 Config File Check

### PostgreSQL — `pg_hba.conf`

```bash
# File location dhundo
sudo find / -name "pg_hba.conf" 2>/dev/null

# File dekho
cat /etc/postgresql/*/main/pg_hba.conf
```

#### ✅ Sahi Config Example:
```
# TYPE  DATABASE   USER   ADDRESS          METHOD
local   all        all                     peer
host    all        all    127.0.0.1/32     md5
host    all        all    ::1/128          md5
host    all        all    0.0.0.0/0        md5    # Remote allow
```

#### ❌ Common Galti — REJECT lines:
```
host    all        all    all              reject   # ← YEH BLOCK KARTA HAI!
```
> 🔴 `reject` ki jagah `md5` ya `scram-sha-256` use karo.

### PostgreSQL — `postgresql.conf`

```bash
# Remote connections allow karne ke liye
listen_addresses = '*'        # default 'localhost' hota hai — change karo
port = 5432
```

```bash
# Changes apply karne ke liye reload
sudo systemctl reload postgresql
```

### Oracle — `tnsnames.ora`

```bash
cat $ORACLE_HOME/network/admin/tnsnames.ora
```

#### Example Entry:
```
MYDB =
  (DESCRIPTION =
    (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP)(HOST = myhost)(PORT = 1521))
    (CONNECT_DATA =
      (SERVER = DEDICATED)
      (SERVICE_NAME = myservice)
    )
  )
```

