## 8. 🛠️ pg_hba.conf Common Issues

| Problem | Reason | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `reject` method | Sabhi connections block | `md5` use karo |
| `peer` auth fail | Remote user local user se match nahi | `md5` use karo |
| IP not matching | Wrong subnet | Correct IP/CIDR likho |
| Changes not applied | Reload nahi kiya | `systemctl reload postgresql` |

---

## 9. ✅ Quick Checklist

Ek ek step follow karo:

- [ ] **Service chal rahi hai?** — `systemctl status postgresql`
- [ ] **Port open hai?** — `netstat -tlnp | grep 5432`
- [ ] **Firewall allow kar raha hai?** — `ufw status`
- [ ] **Username/Password sahi hai?** — `psql -U user -h host`
- [ ] **pg_hba.conf mein `reject` toh nahi?** — Config check karo
- [ ] **`listen_addresses = '*'` set hai?** — `postgresql.conf` check karo
- [ ] **Connection pool full toh nahi?** — `pg_stat_activity` check karo
- [ ] **Logs mein kya error hai?** — `tail -f postgresql.log`

---

> 📌 **Golden Rule:** Hamesha **logs pehle dekho** — wahan exact error hoti hai jo seedha solution bata deti hai.

